<title>UK: Burmah Castrol tumbles on Capel downgrade.</title>
<headline>Burmah Castrol tumbles on Capel downgrade.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-01-09</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares in Burmah Castrol Plc tumbled on Thursday, reversing yesterday's sharp advance, on talk that brokerage HSBC James Capel cut its earnings forecast for the company, dealers said.</p>
<p>At 0842 GMT, the shares were down 25p to 1084p.  </p>
<p>The Capel sector analyst declined to comment, but the brokerage was said to have maintained its neutral rating on the stock.</p>
